## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this vanilla HTML/JavaScript portfolio project.

### Changes Made

**Modified:**
- `index.html` - Added Vercel Analytics script tags to the `<head>` section

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I identified this as a vanilla HTML/JavaScript project and implemented the appropriate analytics code.

**Added Analytics Code:**
1. Analytics initialization script that creates the `window.va` function
2. Deferred script tag that loads the Vercel Analytics script from `/_vercel/insights/script.js`

The analytics code was added after the Google Fonts link and before the main CSS styles in the `<head>` section, ensuring it loads early in the page lifecycle without blocking rendering.

### Code Added (lines 17-20 in index.html):
```html
<script>
  window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="/_vercel/insights/script.js"></script>
```

### Verification Steps Completed

✓ Validated HTML structure integrity (all opening/closing tags balanced)
✓ Confirmed analytics code is properly placed in the `<head>` section
✓ Verified file integrity (no content was lost or corrupted)
✓ Used `defer` attribute to ensure non-blocking script loading

### Framework Detection

This project uses vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript with no build system or package manager (no package.json, node_modules, or framework dependencies). The implementation follows Vercel's vanilla JavaScript instructions.

### Next Steps

Once deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Analytics in the Vercel dashboard sidebar
2. Verify analytics tracking by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/`
3. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard after deployment

### Notes

- No package installation was needed since this is a vanilla HTML project without dependencies
- The `/_vercel/insights/script.js` path is automatically served by Vercel's platform
- Analytics will only track page views when the site is deployed to Vercel (won't work locally)
- The implementation is non-invasive and preserves all existing functionality
